cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a neural network architecture for semantic segmentation of images, which is a task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a random layer and a linear classifier, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of low-power embedded and mobile platforms, which suggests the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper applies the proposed architecture to outdoor scene and aerial image semantic segmentation, which is related to multimedia processing, suggesting the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
